Files:
- plugins/teams/src/teams-api.ts

Context:
Teams has two MSAL token discovery functions that iterate localStorage manually:
```typescript
for (let i = 0; i < localStorage.length; i++) {
  const key = localStorage.key(i);
  if (!key) continue;
  if (key.includes('login.windows.net') && key.includes('accesstoken')) {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem(key);
    // ...
  }
}
```

Replace with:
```typescript
import { findLocalStorageEntry } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';

const entry = findLocalStorageEntry(key => key.includes('login.windows.net') && key.includes('accesstoken'));
if (entry) {
  const parsed = JSON.parse(entry.value);
  // ...
}
```

There may be two separate discovery functions (for different MSAL token types) — replace both.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the token parsing logic — only the localStorage iteration
- Do NOT change any tool files

Files:
- plugins/craigslist/src/craigslist-api.ts

Context:
The callApi function at lines 64-128 has two violations:
1. Raw `fetch()` at line 97 with manual `credentials: 'include'` and `AbortSignal.timeout(30_000)`
2. Manual HTTP error chain at lines 111-127

Replace with:
```typescript
import { fetchFromPage, buildQueryString, getCookie, waitUntil } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';

const callApi = async <T>(
  base: string,
  endpoint: string,
  options: { method?: string; body?: FormData | string; contentType?: string; query?: Record<string, string | number | boolean | undefined>; } = {},
): Promise<T> => {
  if (!isAuthenticated()) throw ToolError.auth('Not authenticated — please log in to Craigslist.');

  const query = { lang: 'en', ...options.query };
  const qs = buildQueryString(query);
  const url = `${base}${endpoint}?${qs}`;

  const headers: Record<string, string> = {};
  const method = options.method ?? 'GET';
  const init: FetchFromPageOptions = { method, headers };

  if (options.body) {
    if (typeof options.body === 'string') {
      headers['Content-Type'] = options.contentType ?? 'application/json';
      init.body = options.body;
    } else {
      init.body = options.body;
    }
  }

  const response = await fetchFromPage(url, init);
  if (response.status === 204) return {} as T;
  return (await response.json()) as T;
};
```

fetchFromPage handles credentials:'include', 30s timeout, and throws httpStatusToToolError on non-ok responses automatically.

Also remove the unused `parseRetryAfterMs` import if it was only used in the manual error chain.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change wapi(), capi(), or accountsApi()
- Do NOT change any tool files
- FormData bodies must still work — fetchFromPage accepts arbitrary RequestInit
